                <p class="u-text u-text-3"> Unreal Engine 4 is truly the rock star of this list. Responsible for games like Fortnite, Player Unknown Battlegrounds, and even the final choice&nbsp;<a href="https://gamerant.com/kingdom-hearts-3-switches-to-unreal-engine-4/" class="u-active-none u-border-none u-btn u-button-style u-hover-none u-none u-text-palette-1-base u-btn-3">for Kingdom Hearts 3</a>, Unreal Engine offers&nbsp;everything you need&nbsp;to make stunning high-quality games.To design a real AAA game you’d likely need a massive team. But that doesn’t mean a small indie studio can’t dive in and start working on something here.Unreal’s graphics capabilities rival CryEngine, but Unreal is more polished and user-friendly.
                </p>
